          <!-- HTML for the Instructions 2 page  -->

    <div class="text">You are about to play the third game. You are the "Human" player on the left, and you can select a number from 1 to 5 by clicking on
      one of the icons. The computer will select a number of its choice as well and the results will be displayed for each round. The rules of the game are explained in the picture below.
      You win if you select a number that is exactly equal to the computer's chocie + 1. Except when the number chosen be either you or the computer is 5; in this case the winning number is 1.
      If the two numbers chosen are not consecutive, then this is considered a tie. Your task in this game is to win as many points as possible against the computer.
    <br/>
    <br/>
    <img id="game3Rules" class="img" src="game3Rules.jpg">
    <br/>
    <br/>
      This game will also have two phases. The first phase is for getting familiar with the game interface, and will consist of 10 trial rounds.
